caption: SO good. Super filling salads and vegan friendly. Outside area is nicely shaded

Mr. Singh, 40, had spent the past year painstakingly and expensively transforming the place after buying it in 2019, and learning the restaurant business “from plumbing to paperwork,” he said. -NY Times  An all-day cafe that serves craft cocktails and wine

I've loved this place for years. They do great cocktails, the food rarely disappoints, the interior is nice and cozy when there isn't covid, and the patio is small but charming and great for an alfresco meal in the summer. I deducted a star because the service is consistently bad and has been for as long as I can remember. The wait staff seems to have no sense of organization and regularly forgets to take your order, doesn't check on you for long periods of time,or you get different servers waiting in the same table causing confusion. If it's busy you might want to skip the service headaches and go somewhere else but as long as it's not too crowded the cocktails, food and ambience are worth the service gamble.
one of my favorite spots in brooklyn please go there and support them through pandemic
Favorite spot on cortelyou road for an occasional glass of wine and light appetizer with a friend. Beautiful staff and atmosphere. Keep up 👾

It is funny...I have passed this place so many times and have eaten in other restaurants in the area, but I never gave this place a second thought. That is until I saw a posting about this restaurant on Instagram. This place is so cute and the staff is so nice and friendly. They have a pretty selective menu and the food I ordered came out fast, fresh and delicious. They also have a heated patio for those that are still not comfortable eating indoors. I will definitely be back soon, if not for dinner, but for brunch.😁
The popcorn chicken and buffalo wings were really good. The tre florella was delicious! Only thing bad was the ranch sauce was very liquidy. Service was a little on the slow side but nothing horrible

Reliably delicious oysters, great wine. The visuals of this spot are beautiful : fresh flowers on every table, beautiful wall art, and a well stacked bar.  Come here for breakfast or brunch: avocado toast (with bacon) and a latte. Or come for dinner: a short menu boast some good eats, and I especially vouch for the burger and old fashioned.  Seating is comfortable and sensible, with indoor and outdoor optional.
Such a cozy place,love to come here with my friends theys always nice and the food taste delicious 👌💖
Service was wonderful, but food was OK.

The food is absolutely splendid, very good quality of ingredients and even thought the menu does not provide a lot of variety, the dishes the place offer are just delicious. I had to give them a 2 star rating based on my experienced, their customer service truly sucks; our server Joseph barely checked on us, our drinks were never refilled, we asked for napkins that were never delivered and we even had to walk to the bar to ask for the bill. During our dining experience we found a hair in our oysters, waited 15 min for the server to come to the table to bring the issue to his attention; The server did apologized that was it, a simple and vague apology. After this terrible experience I don’t think I’ll be coming back, and I recall stating that the food is great and indeed it is, but the portions are designed for a 9 year old and the price doesn’t match it.
Good food, cute patio and friendly service!

The food is not too bad honestly.  Nothing wildly impressive about the menu, but it’s really not too bad.  Decent portion sizes maybe over priced, but I don’t tend to mind because I like being able to dine out in my neighborhood.  Drinks are pretty good too. I don’t know what it is about the server that feels so disingenuous, but I have to say I’m generally not impressed with their service.  Our waiter seemed like he was trying to be polite but his tone didn’t match the words.  We will probably go back just because the vibe is nice enough and the food is okay enough.
Great meal and great service.
As always, the atmosphere of the faux garden an the decor are better than the food. I also prefer the mainstay waitress with the smile that can be seen even behind her mask to the currentl new one.
Small cozy place with beautiful outdoor seating. Delicious food and great finally staff
A class act with a family feel.  Guaranteed love.
Cute and cozy local restaurant. It’s a good place for dinner. One of my favorite dishes is pumpkin soup, all salads, chicken popcorn and more.
Excellent vibe.  Perfect for a good cocktail and food.
Everything is delicious, especially the burger. Super flavorful. They also wrap the food very thoughtfully for delivery — keeping the components separate so nothing got soggy.
Great bartenders and cocktails. Food is good, too

Cool spot for to go drinks. The female bartender was extremely rude and sarcastic. Made a fuss about the out door seating. She will drive customers away. I’ll grab drinks across the street from now on.

The to go drinks are bomb. Unfortunately it is only good with one bar tender. I do not have his name as of yet. However a few times before I went. There where two different bartenders who stiff my wofe and I on some drinks that are in turn are a bit pricey. When we went back our last time. We had a great experience.  Their burgers are one of the best hands down.
Food is good but servings are big and coffee is popular
Nice ambience. Good food and drinks. Friendly staff 😊
It's open late in the hood! Food is heavy.
Cute local spot, delicious fresh food.
This spot provides amazing service as well as yummy food. The best restaurant around town. The drinks and food came out fast and the rates were inexpensive. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Great place to eat, and for cocktails
I cant remember hes name but his last name  is newkirk.  Amazing drinks.
Food and drinks are good. Little bit cold inside, when it’s frizzy outside. The staff is friendly and welcoming.

one of my favorite places in the neighborhood. the tater tots are like little fried bits of mashed potatoes from heaven. I go here regularly and there's always some comedy of errors, but it's still delightful. it's like they're so laid back it makes me more laid back when something inevitably goes wrong with the kitchen or service.
Mussel Mondays. Mussels are plentiful and delicious
Food is always delicious!
Good food and cocktails. Not sure if they still do Monday unlimited mussels!
Couldn't ask for better service. Tiffani, Jack, and Alex were amazing, would 100000 recommend

This place is very cozy and has a "you don't want to leave" vibe, in addition to stylish and tasteful interior design and a nice crowd. The food was great too when we ate in. Unfortunately, there were couple of things to spoil this impression. First, my card was charged twice, and I had to stop by next day (the bar tender went out of her way to help me, thanks for that!:) Secondly, I ordered some food to go, and when I got home, I discovered that the french fries were stale and reheated, which is unacceptable, especially for deep fried dishes. It is a bit annoying to have to double check on things you naturally expect to be done right...
The ambience and service is always on point.

Surely one of the best Brunch spots in Brooklyn! I had the steak and eggs, served with some crispy latke and a perfectly seasoned salad, and indulged in one of their signature cocktails, the Queen T - a refreshing and fulfilling start to my Sunday! Great coffee too! Particularly loved the music - it's like they raided my Spotify account. Highly recommended! Will return
Amazing ambience!!!
The food is always good and the staff is always nice!
Great local neighborhood spot with great service and energy
Nothing extraordinary ordered some expensive roasted peppers and potato balls with some fancy names
Great place and staff!!.... All around awesome... Robin is a dammmnnn good bartender , deff going back AGAIN 😜
Cozy, quaint....
Wonderful European coffee shop vibe. The coffee is good, upscale yet cool, relaxed atmosphere great to work, hang out. Lovely, friendly, service oriented staff!
Place had nice asetectics but trash food. Disappointed in lack of flavor and cost of service.

This was a cool tapas place. Had a great cheese platter and wine. They have indoor and outdoor seating the tables are a little small so it would be a good place for 4 or less people. Great for a date night.
For almost 4 years I have been going to The Castello Plan for brunch hoping things would get better. Unfortunately after all this time I could never get my eggs made right (habitually re-made).
Cozy, tasty bites and good cocktails
Great food

The Castello Plan is a great hang out place troughout the day.  Amazing coffee in the morning, tasty and healthy lunch, great after-work cocktails, lovely side terrace, great brunch food. The owner is a super nice and friendly.  The team is professional and provide fast service.  Highly recommended.
Not so great this last visit. Friendly service, but food was meh.
They offer an awesome range of delicious food. I loved dining here. Employees are always super nice, rates are fair and the spot is always well organised.
good service.good food and excellent service from Marlo
Great place for dinner with friends on the weekend

Castello Plan used to be good but the SERVICE IS AWFUL. Ordered food tonight and they gave the driver the wrong food. They said they would figure it out and call me back. No one called back so when I called THEM back, the answer from the guy on the phone was “He picked up the wrong food. Sorry.” So I guess that’s it? They make a mistake and good luck? No offer to help, send me the correct food, nothing. Cool restaurant man, good luck with it. There’s WAY better places that have opened up on Cortelyou AND they are nice. The food smelled awful anyway - don’t order the chicken sandwich. Yes it was the wrong order but it looked disgusting, soggy.
Love the patio and ambiance of this place but we get almost completely ignored by staff nearly every time we go
Our go to place for cocktails in our neighborhood. Great food. Consistently delivers on a good night out . Highly recommend

The new menu is bland. Just because you add sea salt to the salads, entrees, and beverages doesn't make it flavorful. Staff appeared bored and unwelcoming. Look at the photo of the $16 brunch entree! Looks sad.
The tater tots are not to be missed. Very tasty overall, but with enough salt to keep you thirsty for days.
This is our go-to neighborhood late food spot. Friendly staff. Outdoor seating. Decent drink prices. Delicious food. Did I mention the ice cream?!

Stopped in for a take-out bite to eat earlier tonight. Ordered their plate of nachos to go. Took 25 minutes (possibly more) for the order to come out, and it was missing almost half of the ingredients that were supposed to come with it (such as jalapeños).  25 minutes? Seriously? How long does it take to melt cheese on tortilla chips? Come on now. The place wasn’t even busy.
Food and drinks are good but not always worth the wait. Service is disengaged or overwhelmed, not sure. Stop by but don't be on a time budget.

My husband read some article 15 best brunch places in Brooklyn and this place was not far from us so we decided to go. This place is TERRIBLE. We were the only people at the restaurant and it took 45 minutes to tell me the chef had issues with the Hollandaise  sauce which is super easy to make. They asked if i wanted to order something else or just replace hollandaise with guacamole.  Since my husbands order was already ready i was just put some guacamole.  He is half done with his cold (expensive disgusting burger) and i am still waiting for my food. Finally my food arrives, the salmon was missing, guacamole was on only one piece of toast and poached eggs were raw and disgusting looking. I returned my food  and my husband couldn't finish the raw cold burner (request medium well doneness) with cold fries. How this place is considered excellent when they cannot make poached eggs and hollandaise sauce is ridiculous. It took over an hour to get everything on the table and we could not even eat the food and had to walk out.

We've come here often for drinks (solid cocktails, interesting wine list, nice happy hour specials) and the service and ambiance are always top notch, really nice. I don't know what happened, but our dinner last night was so so bad. The salad was overwhelmingly salty and way too skimpy for the price. The mussels smelled strongly, to the point where we wondered if they had gone bad: their taste was subpar but at least not rotten. The chicken wings were dry with mediocre flavor, and even the chips seemed overcooked! It was so disappointing, we really couldn't believe how bad it was, and how expensive for the quality and quantity of food. Next time we'll just stick to the drinks!
What a fantastic place. & Robin the bartender is the best!

(Translated by Google) Delicious delicious food, excellent service, friendly and courteous staff, tasty and fresh and spicy food and good variety of good opening dishes, excellent main courses, especially the burger or chicken sandwich, I recommend not to give up dessert because I tasted them all and they are really great, , Has been a few times that I am there and I always enjoy very much, strongly recommend to everyone  (Original) אוכל טעים בטירוף, שירות מעולה, צוות חביב ואדיב, אוכל טעים וטרי ומתובל טוב מגוון של מנות פתיחה טובות, מנות עיקריות מעולות, בפרט הבורגר או הכריך עוף, אני ממליץ לא לוותר על קינוח כי טעמתי את כולם והם ממש מעולים, בהחלט אהבתי את המקום,כבר כמה פעמים שאני שם ואני תמיד נהנה מאוד, ממליץ בחום לכולם

Love this place. Been there a few times now. Did some Birthday drinks there recently. Had a blast. Drinks are delicious and made with care (try the Penicillan). Food is yummy (Castello Tots are a revelation). Staff are lovely. Atmos top notch - warm and cosy. Good times!

I love maps and the Castello Plan is a map and restaurant! Check it out on wiki. We had brunch here last weekend, I loved the eggs chachouka! The cortelyou is cute with the fresh OJ and grapefruit. I always love a cocktail and tried a few, the Bourbon Renewal was my fave even though I'm normally a rum girl. The boozy brunch which was great value for around $20 for unlimited booze! Definately worth a visit if you fancy cocktails and a good environment.

I have no comment at this time. First I asked for a sample of a beer for my fiance and they forgot. Then we waited forever for the bill.  Then our waitress made an about face while I was bringing the bill back to her with payment. No wonder people were complaining about waiting an hour for their food

Service is very sub par for any location, especially NY. Besides being slow, no attention to their customers. Waiting for food for over an hour. Asking for update results in "it's on the way" response and no other updates. Wanted to like the place.
Really enjoyed my bottomless brunch. And the service was great. Worth a visit.

VAGUELY MEDITERRANEAN in its offerings, The Castello Plan is easy to miss surveying Cortelyou Road’s rich array of ethnic cuisine. The venue’s sole sign is eye level and a dull metal color the size of an overly large dinner plate, which is fully inconsistent with The Plan’s mix of small plates and smattering of light, inexpensive entrees. The food appeals, the drinks are pleasant and the seating — inside and outside, in what locals before gentrification surely saw as an alleyway — is cramped.

I am so happy to have chosen this restaurant! My wife and I were served amazing cocktails, along with some of the best buffalo wings and steak tartare. Also, the oysters were so good, I ordered a second dozen! If you're in the neighborhood, this place is a really great spot!

Cocktails were pretty good and beer and wine was reasonably priced, but we ended up not eating our food. The eggplant sandwich was eggplant as bread, and the eggplant was very oily and soggy. Also the only salad had honey lime dressing which was so sweet and tasted like lime soda.

Enjoy myself every time I go. The bottomless brunch is a good value. Each cocktail is made fresh - they even make the OJ for the mimosas... No mixers here! I've also been for taco Tuesday. I highly recommend the fish tacos. The service has been good and friendly each time. It's in the area and I am happy to support a solid local business.

Five of us went and five of us left wishing we had gone elsewhere. The drinks did not come out for almost 30 min. They changed the nachos from amazing creamy stewed mushroom nachos to now very boring bean and cheese ones (nachos are MUCH better across the street at Cinco de Mayo). The salad was meh (my friend didn’t finish it), my tater tots were at best, not too bad, the eggplant sandwich was ridiculous (the BREAD for the sandwich is fried eggplant—cute idea, not great execution) and it had too much spinach on it. Also the cocktails were just ok when they came out. I don’t think I’ll go back any time soon (we largely all agreed on this) and I’ve lived in the hood for a long time.
Cocktails and service
Simply amazing. Cannot miss - perfect place to chill at!
Cosy atmosphere, great cocktails and very friendly staff.
Best Hot Toddy's on Cortelyou. Also the beet salad was amazing
My boyfriend inhaled his fried chicken sandwich. My nachos were so yum. Nice wine selection. Music here is super eclectic.
Good Bar, Great Service - Tasty Drinks. A great bar with the bartenders to match.
Odd food selection. Service okay to subpar. Food eh. Nice quiet place.
very slow service, they dont tell you how long you have to wait 🤦🏽‍♀️they don't make you feel welcome at all.
Great bar serving very tasty cocktails !
Quality food
Nice place

The food was okay but a little expensive, but the service was unbearably slow. An hour to get our drinks, an hour and a half for food. The atmosphere was nice and the staff was pleasant, but that wait is just too long.
Good food, great bartender, very cool ambiance
Great spot. Very solid
Amazing place
The Castello Plan is a very solid spot.
Overpriced and no variety.

(Translated by Google) A nice bar where you can nibble something of good quality. Pretty minimalist as to the place but for more cozy. The price is expensive but the quality is there.  (Original) Un bar sympa où on peut grignoter quelque chose de bonne qualité. Assez minimaliste quant à la place mais pour plus de cosy. Le prix reste cher mais la qualité est là.
Delicious cocktails

10/2018. What happened to the food here?? We used to come nearly every weekend for brunch, we liked it so much. But this past summer the food got... Just not very good. The potatoes are mealy and bland, the mesclun has no dressing of any kind. Everything is just kind of blah. I hope they go back to their old, more flavorful cooking style. I don't think we'll come much anymore.  I generally like this place. The interior design is very pleasing, and the food is good. The music is good but too loud, so I end up going less often than I would like to. It's hard to talk over.  12/2017 edit: The music volume during weekend brunch has been tolerable for the last few times we've been. It's nice to be able to talk without shouting. Thank you, I hope you keep it this way!
when i lived in ditmas this was my favorite spot. cute outdoor space and cozy in the winter.
Popped in here pre show for a quick bite and a drink. Tasty homemade tots and impressive by the glass selections, including a wonderful dry Tokay. I'll be back!
Perfect little neighborhood French bistro. Surprisingly good, yet short, wine list. Wednesday specials that push you past hump day.
Hi this is Miriam from the Brooklyn Agency saying Hi! it is a real pleasure working with you!!!!!

Rustic, simple, and good food. It can definitely get loud, and it’s better if you are only a party of two because the tables are small. The food is pretty consistent and balanced. If you don’t want to do dishes, this is a good spot to get a basic meal and enjoy it.

Nice place, I like the decorations. They have a nice menu of drinks n they have very good n juice burger it's a little bit a price but its Deserved)) we got a cheese plate with prosciutto and jelly, and I think it's a nachos
One of my favs....service never disappoints! Ask for Erin or Arturo! Total #baes

Your friendly neighborhood spot. Like the atmosphere there. Not fancy, place where you always will feel yourself comfy. Food is good and nice collection of wine and cocktails. You will definitely enjoy your time there.

Amazing place for any occasion, or no occasion needed at all. Just come and enjoy great drinks, great food and friendly staff. I've been coming here since place opened. And it only got better. Have you tried their tacos?! Amazing! Extra cheers to best bartender ever - Eryn!!!

Nice place. Waiter service was good. 30 minutes to get food on table, but the food was fresh. Overpriced. I paid $21 for spring gnocchi that didn't fill me up (very, very small plate), I had to get the beef taco ($5), which was decent. My friend got a burger ($16) with a few fries ($2) for cheese.  They had a deal for shot & beer for $8 which wasn't bad. All in all, in conclusion, it  wasn't worth the $82 bucks I spent for 2 people. This is a place you take a date on. Oh and the cocktail list was pretty impressive. Not your ordinary cocktails, its mixologist stuff. Averaging about 14 bucks each.
Everything is perfect
I found the food to be quite expensive. Drinks were a good price. Ambiance and character of the place was great.

Amazing date night spot. A small menu, but after multiple visits I can attest to all of your options being wonderful. The cocktails are also delightful, and range wide enough for everyone to find something.

I enjoyed a two cocktails at there bar. Robin was the bartender at the time and boy does HE know his craft. A nice raspberry gin cocktail that went down way to smoothly and an aviation (One of my favorite cocktails) balanced to perfection. Though I did not eat there, the food looked tasty coming from the kitchen.

Excellent cocktails and delicious menu!! I just had a Bloody Mary with prociutto, cheese, and blue cheese stuffed olives!!  Robin, our bartender, was the best!  Really cool dude - he made delicious gin cocktails (especially a great Aviation) for my husband. Will definitely be back!!
Went there for a brunch yesterday. It was delish! The place has a cute outdoor area and was not overcrowded. Will come back again!
Love this spot - get the mushroom crostini
Great food and cocktails.
Excellent wine, food, and service. Thanks on our pre Valentine's day.
Wonderful spot for dinner or just a drink.  Brunch is excellent too!
A few friends and I had an event there last weekend with a fixed price menu. The waiters were attentive. The place is small but  managebly so. The food was good. Try the french toast.
Cute place but don’t get the logger
Chef can accommodate dietary restrictions.
Great food. Kitchen open late. Very cozy with friendly staff.
Amazing service ! Really great atmosphere and location, fantastic brunch and if anyone likes spicy drinks please try their Calabaza Pasadilla. Truly recommend to anyone who enjoys perfection :)
Cute space, good food, drinks, good tunes plating

still great atmosphere and wonderful staff, the burgers however change still good but not special as before. The bread is diferent, no mustard leaves and the fries are not the same. The sauce is regular ketchup not like before.
Great atmosphere
Great cocktails and service very friendly
What's with all the GARBAGE reviews from "local guides"?
Exoctic wine selection. Phenomenal fine dining and great atmosphere
Love it.
Fun vibe. Great happy hour cocktails.
I loved the place. Food was tasty and fresh in the middle of an unrelated ambience. You should try the experience.
Friendly, intimate, small but not cramped, outdoor seating
The food was delicious—however, the space is very TIGHT.
Food was great. And the homemade salt caramel ice cream ❤❤
Never had a bad bite of food here!
Amazing. Minimalist but delicious.

Absolutely terrible service. Not crowded, yet it took 45mins to get a salad. The salad we ordered was not at all what we expected, as it was very far from the same salad we had ordered just 2 months prior. Perhaps a new chef? The drinks on the other hand are excellent. The Hump Day happy hour special is worth it. Otherwise, overpriced for mediocre food and less than acceptable service.

Decent enough brunch options and they are willing to make adjustments to the recipes according to your preferences. Fits well with the ever growing hipster crowd in this locality though surprisingly they only have one kind of coffee! The challah french toast is soft (but has no fruits-only cream and jam!), the croque madame looks great and the breakfast plan feels wholesome. Their drinks are decent too. You could grab seats for a party of 6 at a time too- so that's good if you are catching up with friends. Service has definitely improved over the years but one minus star for one food-poisoning instance.

This place is AMAZING!!! I moved to Flatlands from Astoria and was looking around for something that reminded me of my favorite neighborhood. Cortelyou Road is a short cab ride from my new home, and I decided to try The Castello Plan. I had their Temprañillo, cauliflower soup, pumpkin gnocchi and homemade ice cream. Everything was delicious and the service is top notch! I'm in love and will become a regular here!

I came here for brunch with my girlfriend and her parents. The ambiance is lovely, and I dig the decor a lot, but the food was pretty unremarkable. I returned a few weeks later for dinner with aforementioned girlfriend, and had the same experience. Given the prices, I'd expect a lot better. Back to the farm!
Food was just average for an eatery. Did not get a Caribbean feel or taste in food. Our jerk chicken tasted and looked like smothered chicken.
Small, comfortable neighborhood restaurant with very comfort style brunch menu.
Very cozy with nice happy hour specials. Great for a winter night
Great local restaurant. Try mushroom crostini, mussels, gazpacho, fish tacos, signature cocktails. Kitchen is open late.
The food is a bit pricey but definitely worth it.
Delicious food, especially the burgers! Paired with great cocktails and wine.

Called a little after 7pm to verify that they had all you can eat mussels. We arrived a little after 8 and were told they ran out. We were a little shocked that a huge draw could just not be well planned for, but figured we could just find something else and be happy. Cocktails were lovely, but service was incredibly slow. Our 2nd round of cocktails was served as our dessert course it came so late. The food took quite a while also. We just felt forgotten about and though fine, the food wasn't enough to overcome the general disappointment of the experience. This was not our first visit either.
Pretentious, but so am I :P Good food, great cocktails, well designed. Supt cozy and somewhat overpriced.
Ordered the Croque Madame and Bloody Mary for brunch and all I can say is that it was AMAZING! Great food and drinks, awesome atmosphere, and friendly service. We will definitely be back!!
Close and comfort!!!

This place is super cute and I always have great service. I've had a few small issues here and there (overcooked egg or glass with lipstick on it), but nothing that really takes away from this cute neighborhood gem. Also, I love the nerdy name and the fact that they have a copy of the Castello Plan hanging in the seating area.
Great atmosphere. Cute outdoor space. Great for dates.
Good place for wine.. Price is a little much.. But I enjoy it
Best burgers and a awesome french toast for brunch

Cocktails were fantastic and inventive. Had burger and salad which were excellent. Waitress was alone and over-taxed with the number of patrons but really was working hard, so not her fault. The perfect weather to sit outside undoubtedly helped my perceptions. Pricing was high-ish but not terrible for the quality, though dessert felt like a gouge. Realistically should get about 4 1/2 stars.
a very cozy and romantic spot for dinner and/or drinks.
Every time we have been here, the food has been nothing short of amazing. The rustic atmosphere and pleasant staff make it an enjoyable experience each and every time.
Delicious!!
Pricey and not that great.

Everything here is great. The menu is small, but tasty, there is a huge drink selection and although the place is always busy, the staff is great. One of the only places in the neighborhood to have drinks in a bar setting that also serves food.

Good service and simply a nice spot for a wine as well as a breakfast. Delicious food!! A bit too tight in space. Maybe one less table would make it a better space but id also sacrifice that star for a less expensive spot. :)

It's high time I wrote this review, given that this has been my home-base restaurant for over 2 years. Get the burger. Go to brunch and get the French toast. Or the bagel with house cured salmon. Or go on a Monday night and get all you can eat mussels or on a Wednesday night and get the best cocktails around for $7. And sit for hours on end because they won't ever hurry you out.
great little place in Brooklyn.  food is delicious and the staff is great. intimate spot with wonderful lighting at night and bright and sunny for weekend brunch.  well done.
Excellent farm fresh ingredients made with care...

Very cute place for drinks and cheese. And getting so much better during the winter when they open the yard and let you sit outside. I was there last Friday, and enjoyed the place. We had few cocktails, and plate of cheese, and enjoy a friendly atmosphere. There are few other nice places in the block, so you can try a different place after.
(Translated by Google) The food is delicious if a hot coffee  (Original) Esta rica la comida  si un cafecito bien caliente
great service, very comfortable environment, food was good

My favorite bar/restaurant on Cortelyou Road.  They have $10 all you can eat mussels on Mondays.  There's also an oyster happy hour on the weekends.  Also, they have really good small dishes that are made to order behind the bar.  The staff are all very friendly and there's a cute patio outside.

The staff is fantastic - true professionals who are classy and friendly. Food is great. Small selection, but somehow just the right combination of options. Cocktails, wine, beer - wonderful. Beautiful decor, great use of cozy space.
Friendly staff and delicious food choices in a fun setting.

They do not serve any entrees. The "Plan" is to charge a lot of money for small plates of appetizers, so that you will buy many many appetizers! Clever, right? You will spend more, on those, than on 1 substantial entree at a regular restaurant.
Great atmosphere, nice staff, decent food (though on the pricy end) and short wait times (Sunday brunch at 1230). Also has a little outside seating area.

Went here for a 3rd Date and I love it,  I must confess that I dont know much about the food and wine but the waitress was very helpful wonderful atmosphere the house wines are excellent the apetizers are marvelously put together a blend of different flavors on every bite. Its great little place hope this help others, cause diffinately I will be back
Pleasant all around; decent food, good wine, and very nice staff.
I've brunched here a few times. The food has always been really quite good, but the selection is limited. Coffee is terrible and overpriced.

This is our new favorite Cortelyou road eatery. It's not exactly cheap, but then again, neither are most spots on Cortelyou - and the beer and wine list here blows everyone else out of the water. Nice mix of small plates and entrees, which also trend on the small side, but are so incredibly delicious it's hard to complain. The wait staff is always friendly, but not TOO friendly, and very knowledgable about the entire menu, as well as the beer and wine list.
